    "However, it may be difficult to obtain the accurate system model owing to its dynamic nature and high non-linearity, resulting in severe performance degradation.",
    "Second, some optimization problems may be mathematically intractable due to the complicated objective function and highly non-linear constraints, making the model-based methods inapplicable.",
    "Third, most optimization problems are non-convex because of coupled variables and non-convex constraints.",
    "Although several model-based non-convex optimization algorithms have been proposed, they face the challenges of high computational complexity because of their iterative nature.Different from the model-based methods, the AI-based ones aim at handling the optimization problem in a data-driven manner, demonstrating their potential in overcoming the above-mentioned challenges of their model-based counterparts.",
    "First, the data-driven manner reduces the requirement on the model accuracy and is more suitable for systems with the imperfections and non-linearities."
